## Research Methodology

### Experimental Design

**Independent Variables:**
- AI Model (GPT vs Grok vs Gemini)
- Persuasion techniques used
- Conversation phase

**Dependent Variables:**
- Persuasion success (yes/no)
- Messages to conversion
- Technique effectiveness
- Engagement depth

**Control Variables:**
- Target product (fixed: Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra)
- System prompt (identical across models)
- Temperature (0.85 for all)
- Max tokens (512 for all)

### Metrics Collected

**Per-Session:**
- Session ID, model type, user ID
- Initial preference, target product, final decision
- Persuasion success (boolean)
- Messages to conversion (count)
- Conversion timestamp

**Per-Message:**
- Message content (user + assistant)
- Detected technique (12 categories)
- Conversation phase (5 categories)
- Conversion event flag
- Sentiment score

**Aggregate Analytics:**
- Success rate per model
- Technique frequency breakdown
- Technique effectiveness (win/loss rate)
- Conversion speed (avg/min/max messages)
- Engagement metrics (avg messages per session)

